title: macbook air 820-00165 stuck 0.284 mA
message:
Hello, I have a MacBook air 13 a1466 2017. which had liquid damage, I corrected the u7600 which was oxidized and the machine started up again, after 10 days it started to show a problem again without turning on, freezing at 0.284 mA, I changed the u7600 once which had liquid damage, but did not start working again, remained stuck at 0.284 mA.

measurements taken.
PM_SLP - 0.0V
PPBUS_G3H - 8.56v
PPBUS_S5_HS_COMPUTING_ISNS - 8.56v
PPBUS_S5_HS_OTHER_ISNS - 8.56v
PP3V42_G3H - 3.42v
PPVRTC_G3H - 3.3v
PP5V_S5 - 5v
PP5V_S4RS3 - 5v
PP5V_S0 - 5v
PP3V3_S5 - 3.3v
PP3V3_S4 - 3.3v
PP3V3_SUS - 3.3v
PP3V3_S3 - 3.3v
PP3V3_S0 - 3.3v
PP1V8_S3 - 1.8v
PP1V2_S3 - 1.2v
PP1V05_SUS - 1.15v
PP1V5_S0 - not present
PP0V6_S0_DDRVTT - not present
PP1V05_S0 - 0.24v
PP1V05_S0SW_PCH_HSIO - 0.24v
PPVCC_S0_CPU - not present
PP1V05_S0 - 1.68V
I would like to remind you that the CPU is heating up.

What do you recommend me to do? I'm a little lost on what to check.

title: macbook air 820-00165 stuck 0.284 mA
message:
Fist check diode mode to ground on the missing S0 voltages.

As you get 3V3/5V_S=, PM_SLP_S3_BUF_L is OK.
Check if R8185 is good.
Also post U7870 voltages.

and one more detail now, I measured ppbus_g3h again and now I only have 2.3V. Returning this information is important because yesterday's measurement was normal, for some reason I don't have normal voltage now.
